<h2>Exploding Sequence</h2><div id="problem_icons" class="noprint"><a href="minimal=492"><img src="images/icons/file_html.png" title="Show HTML problem content" class="icon"></a>&nbsp;<span class="tooltip"><img src="images/icons/info.png" class="icon"><span class="tooltiptext_right">Published on Saturday, 6th December 2014, 01:00 pm; Solved by 410;<br>Difficulty rating: 60%</span></span></div><div id="problem_info"><h3>Problem 492</h3></div>
<div class="problem_content" role="problem">
<p>Define the sequence $a_1, a_2, a_3, \dots$ as:</p>
<ul><li>$a_1 = 1$</li>
<li>$a_{n+1} = 6a_n^2 + 10a_n + 3$ for $n \ge 1$.</li>
</ul><p>
Examples:<br>
$a_3 = 2359$<br>
$a_6 = 269221280981320216750489044576319$<br>
$a_6 \bmod 1\,000\,000\,007 = 203064689$<br>
$a_{100} \bmod 1\,000\,000\,007 = 456482974$
</p>

<p>
Define $B(x,y,n)$ as $\sum (a_n \bmod p)$ for every prime $p$ such that $x \le p \le x+y$.
</p>

<p>
Examples:<br>
$B(10^9, 10^3, 10^3) = 23674718882$<br>
$B(10^9, 10^3, 10^{15}) = 20731563854$
</p>

<p>Find $B(10^9, 10^7, 10^{15})$.</p>

</div><br>
<br>
